<!-- Header -->
<%= render 'layouts/header' %>

<div class="container mx-auto my-10 p-10 bg-white rounded shadow-lg">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center">About the Project</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg p-4">
    This project utilizes data from various sources, including the World of
    Warcraft Game Data API, the official World of Warcraft website, and the
    Faker library, to provide insights into the World of Warcraft game dynamics.
    With a focus on collecting and presenting data related to game races,
    classes, specializations, and heroes, our aim is to offer players a
    comprehensive resource for understanding the intricate details of their
    favorite game characters and abilities, aiding in strategy development and
    enhancing their gameplay experience.
  </p>

  <!-- Data Source -->
  <div class="container mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 p-4">
    <!-- API Data Source -->
    <div
      class="flex flex-col space-y-4 justify-between bg-white rounded shadow p-6 hover:shadow-md duration-300 ease-in-out"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Game Data API</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 flex-1">
        Provides game data including races, classes, and specializations. The API returns JSON objects with fields like `name` and `id`, and nested objects for complex attributes.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://develop.battle.net/documentation/world-of-warcraft-classic/game-data-apis"
        target="_blank"
        class="rounded-md bg-indigo-600 px-3.5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-indigo-500"
        >API Documentation</a
      >
    </div>

    <!-- Official Website Data Source -->
    <div
      class="flex flex-col space-y-4 justify-between bg-white rounded shadow p-6 hover:shadow-md duration-300 ease-in-out"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Official Website</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 flex-1">
        Data including race images and descriptions are extracted from the official website and structured into a CSV file with columns for `id`, `name`, `faction`, `description`, and `media_url`.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://worldofwarcraft.blizzard.com/en-us/game/races"
        target="_blank"
        class="rounded-md bg-indigo-600 px-3.5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-indigo-500 mt-auto"
        >Official Website</a
      >
    </div>

    <!-- Faker Library Data Source -->
    <div
      class="flex flex-col space-y-4 justify-between bg-white rounded shadow p-6 hover:shadow-md duration-300 ease-in-out"
    >
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Faker Library</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 flex-1">
        Generates fake character names and quotes for placeholder data in development. Used for populating the `Heroes` table with dummy data.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/faker-ruby/faker/blob/main/doc/games/world_of_warcraft.md"
        target="_blank"
        class="rounded-md bg-indigo-600 px-3.5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-indigo-500"
        >Faker GitHub</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Integration Plan Section -->
  <div class="container mx-auto px-8 py-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Data Integration Plan</h2>
    <p>This project integrates data from several sources to create a comprehensive view of the World of Warcraft universe:</p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-4">
      <li>
        <strong>Game Data API</strong> provides the core structure for races, classes, and specializations.
        This forms the foundation of our database where all other data references.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Official Website</strong> enriches the basic data with detailed descriptions and media,
        linked by race ID. Images and texts are used to add a visual dimension to the API data.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Faker Library</strong> is used to simulate user-generated content, such as hero profiles and quotes,
        to demonstrate how user input might interact with the core data structure.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each race and class from the API is mapped to its corresponding image and description from the website.
      Specializations are tied to classes and extended with roles and additional attributes.
      The heroes are dynamically generated to showcase a variety of race and class combinations, with placeholder data
      demonstrating potential real-world character descriptions and commentary.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Database Tables Structure -->
  <div class="container mx-auto my-10 p-10 bg-white rounded shadow-lg">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Database Tables and Columns</h2>
    <!-- Database Table Structures -->
    <!-- Races Table-->
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Races Table</h3>
      <table class="min-w-full bg-white rounded-lg shadow overflow-hidden">
        <thead class="bg-gray-700 text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="w-1/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Column Name
            </th>
            <th class="w-3/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Description
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-gray-700">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The primary key of the races table.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">name</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The name of the race.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">faction</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The faction of the race (Alliance or Horde).
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">description</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">A brief description of the race.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">media_url</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">The URL of the race media image.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- PlayerClasses Table-->
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">PlayerClasses Table</h3>
      <table class="min-w-full bg-white rounded-lg shadow overflow-hidden">
        <thead class="bg-gray-700 text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="w-1/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Column Name
            </th>
            <th class="w-3/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Description
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-gray-700">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The primary key of the player_class table.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">name</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The name of the class.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">power_type</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The type of power the class uses (e.g., mana, rage).
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">media_url</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">
              A URL to an associated media item, like an image, for the class.
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Heroes Table-->
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Heroes Table</h3>
      <table class="min-w-full bg-white rounded-lg shadow overflow-hidden">
        <thead class="bg-gray-700 text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="w-1/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Column Name
            </th>
            <th class="w-3/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Description
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-gray-700">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The unique identifier for the hero.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">player_class_id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The identifier that links the hero to a class.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">race_id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The identifier that links the hero to a race.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">name</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">
              The hero's name.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">quote</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">
              A quote associated with the hero.
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Specialization Table-->
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Specialization Table</h3>
      <table class="min-w-full bg-white rounded-lg shadow overflow-hidden">
        <thead class="bg-gray-700 text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="w-1/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Column Name
            </th>
            <th class="w-3/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Description
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-gray-700">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The unique identifier for the specialization.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">player_class_id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The identifier linking the specialization to its corresponding class.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">name</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              The name of the specialization.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">description</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">
              A detailed description of the specialization.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">role</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4">
              The role that the specialization plays in the game (e.g., healer, tank, damage dealer).
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- RaceClass Table-->
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">RaceClass Table</h3>
      <table class="min-w-full bg-white rounded-lg shadow overflow-hidden">
        <thead class="bg-gray-700 text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="w-1/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Column Name
            </th>
            <th class="w-3/4 px-6 py-3 text-left uppercase tracking-wider">
              Description
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-gray-700">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">race_id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              A foreign key to the race table, indicating which race is associated with the class.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">player_class_id</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
              A foreign key to the player class table, indicating which class is associated with the race.
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<!-- Footer -->
<%= render 'layouts/footer' %>
